25|$|The UK did, however, {{ratify the}} {{predecessor}} to the 1968 Treaty: <b>The</b> <b>Geneva</b> <b>Convention</b> on Road Traffic. Technically, the country identifier design is not compliant with <b>the</b> 1949 <b>Geneva</b> <b>Convention</b> on Road Traffic (Annex 4) which requires the classic white oval design to be displayed. For many countries <b>the</b> <b>Geneva</b> <b>Convention</b> has been superseded by the later Vienna Convention on Road Traffic; EU {{states that have}} ratified the latter must therefore comply with Council Regulation 2411/98, which necessitates {{the use of the}} EU symbol.|$|R
