25|$|The 2009 {{budget of}} the ICRC amounts more than 1 billion Swiss francs. Most of that money comes from the States, {{including}} Switzerland in its capacity as the depositary state of <b>the</b> <b>Geneva</b> <b>Conventions,</b> from national Red Cross societies, the signatory states of <b>the</b> <b>Geneva</b> <b>Conventions,</b> and from international organizations like the European Union. All payments to the ICRC are voluntary and are received as donations based on two types of appeals issued by the Committee: an annual Headquarters Appeal to cover its internal costs and Emergency Appeals for its individual missions.|$|E
